{
  "texts": [
    "The lower layers tend to learn shallow syntactic patterns, whereas the downstream (higher) layers tend to learn semantic patterns of global context.",
    "Hence, each layer can capture various levels of abstraction, learn hierarchical representations from low-level features to high-level semantics, and promote modular learning.",
    "Multiple layers increase the model's capacity to combine and transform information flowing through the layers in complex ways to capture intricate and non-linear relationships among the tokens, including information from distant tokens in the input sequence.",
    "Each position of the input context window has an identical but independent and fully connected FFNN.",
    "Each FFNN of the GPT-3 architecture uses two hidden layers, each with four times the number of nodes as there are dimensions of the input vectors."
  ]
}